<h2>Canvas or SVG</h2>

<p>Should you use <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code>? Visually, canvas and SVG output the same exact image with Zdog. But in practice, they each have their benefits.</p>

<p><strong>Canvas</strong> is better for lots of shapes and smaller image sizes. Canvas renders on a flat image, so it doesn't have to manage a DOM. But its rendered with pixels, so it can be slower with larger sizes ‚Äî particularly with high-resolution screens.</p>

<p><strong>SVG</strong> is better for fewer shapes and larger image images. SVG is a vector format, so its resolution independent, perfect for large image sizes. However, all shapes have to be rendered and sorted with individual DOM elements, which can negatively impact performance and get your fan spinning.</p>

